ee's nonprofit education reform group\n* [http://www.tntp.org/ The New Teacher Project]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081209002125/http://www.nctq.org/p/about/boardMember.jsp?name=Advisory%20Board%20Member%20-%20Rhee Bio on National Council on Teacher Quality]\n* [http://www.makers.com/michelle-rhee Michelle Rhee]  Video produced by ''[[Makers: Women Who Make America]]''\n* [https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=14151155 \"Michelle Rhee: 'You Can Change People's Hope'\"] National Public Radio, 2007-09-04\n* {{C-SPAN|michellerhee}}\n* {{cite news |title=Schoolhouse Rock: D.C. education chief says school choice shouldn't be reserved for the rich |first=Collin |last= Levy|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=December 22, 2007 |quote=I believe we should proliferate what's working and close down what's not. Period.}}\n* [http://www.pmakid.com/2011/09/michelle-rhee-former-chancellor-of-dc.html Interview with Michelle Rhee on PMAKid.com]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-npo}}\n{{s-new|rows=2|office}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chief Executive Officer of [[The New Teacher Project]]|years=1997\u20132007}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Arlela Rozman]]}}\n|-\n{{s-ttl|title=Chief Executive Officer of [[StudentsFirst]]|years=2010\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Clifford Janey]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chancellor of [[District of Columbia Public Schools]]|years=2007\u20132010}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Kaya Henderson]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rhee, Michelle}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American educators of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American nonprofit executives]]\n[[Category:American people of South Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American women of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American school administrators]]\n[[Category:American schoolteachers]]\n[[Category:Cornell University alumni]]\n[[Category:District of Columbia Public Schools]]\n[[Category:John F. Kennedy School of Government alumni]]\n[[Category:Politicians 